attributes.title: GRAND THEFT AUTOMATIC PAINT ROLLER
attributes.caption: THIS PLACE COULD USE A LITTLE SPRUCING UP
attributes.description:
It's PRIME TIME. AMAZON PRIME TIME. Amazon is well known for being a great service to obtain items in a quick and timely manner. With this new show not only do we put that to the test, but we venture into what Amazon is all about, the weird stuff.

The rules are simple, using our collective funds we buy a few items for each other and not knowing what they are, we share them with one another on the couch. We could very well go poor doing this, we just want you to know this.

attributes.title: LUBE SHOT ROULETTE
attributes.caption: TASTES LIKE A TINGLY SCREWDRIVER
attributes.description: It's PRIME TIME.... well sort of. With James down for the count we play with the Amazon item he bought for today's episode without him; a drinking game called, DROP SHOT; a game of chance where a sizable container of alcohol is administered at random to an unlucky turn-taker. But, James never intended for us to play the game with only alcohol, that's why he also bought a bevy of flavored lubricants, which may (or may not) be edible, as mixers  After we throw in some soda, sriracha, and expired orange juice, James might not be too bummed to have sat this one out.

attributes.title: $30 MASSAGER VS $200 MASSAGER
attributes.caption: THAT WAS MY ASSHOLE!!!
attributes.description: After the great stunt work by James.  Alec's has been dying to get onto the skateboard and give his hand at stunts.

attributes.title: BEST DANCING ROBOTS OF AMAZON
attributes.caption: CAN YOU PROGRAM IT TO CHOKE PEOPLE OUT?
attributes.description: Aleks and his lab assistant, Alec, return to regale us with their duo style comedic antics on another Amazon Test Lab episode. What wacky, wild, wondrous situation will these two crazy buffoons get into today I wonder! The potential is truly limitless.

attributes.title: CAN A MONITOR STOP A BULLET?
attributes.caption: WHO TAUGHT YOU HOW TO AIM?!?!?
attributes.description:
With the news that some kid had his MSI monitor stop a bullet that was shot at his house, naturally we had to try it our selves.  Luckily we had the help from a trained professional to help us handle the weapons.  But of course this Cow Chop we're talking about, so why would anything go to plan?

Do not try this at home.  We are under the supervision of trained professionals.
attributes.display_title: CAN A MONITOR STOP A BULLET?

attributes.title: YAMAHA SEASCOOTER VS THE PACIFIC OCEAN
attributes.description: Aleks and Alec make a long trek to the beach in order to test out some fresh items available for purchase on Amazon Prime.
